// folder, this candidate was NOT broken. It was superseded: sinc_v7
// (SplinePhaseSinc, still live in ../SplinePhaseSinc.cs) does the same job -
// a small fixed phase table instead of near-exact per-phase computation -
// but fits a per-tap natural cubic spline across the phase axis instead of
// blending whole kernels with one shared 4-point Lagrange weight. Measured
// (2026-07-07): with HALF the stored phases (16 vs this candidate's 32),
// sinc_v7 tied sinc_v5 on every scenario and beat it by ~10.5 dB SNR on the
// Music scenario (69.77 dB vs 59.32 dB). Since sinc_v7 had no scenario where
// it lost, and used fewer resources doing it, keeping both as live A/B
// candidates stopped teaching anything new - this record exists so the
// rubato-style "blend whole kernels" technique and the measured comparison
// against r8brain's "per-tap spline" technique are not lost.
